text.tspan: oscillatory brain activity during nREM sleep
Verna Heikkinen, Mia Liljestrm, Sampsa Vanhatalo, Leena Lauronen, Hanna Renvall
The promising results demonstrate that bayesian latent variable models are applicable to low-resolution and often noise-prone clinical EEG data
Future studies with longitudinal data sets are needed to establish whether M/EEG fingerprints are consistent over developmental periods.
Using higher-density EEG measurements and additional clinical covariates could reveal oscillatory patterns related to neurological disorders or brain function in general.
